text.value: Please summarize the Azure REST API specifications Readme

The README files in the Azure/azure-rest-api-specs GitHub repository provide various information about specific tools, SDK configurations, example scenarios, and guidelines related to the usage and development of APIs within Azure's services. Each README is tailored to its directory or file's purpose, offering insights into specific Azure products or the technical details necessary for working with the APIs related to those products.

In general, these README documents guide contributors and users on how to manage API specifications, use service-level configurations, reference material, and utilize the development tools provided. They also include examples and test cases for better understanding and managing different Azure services through their REST API interfaces.

Since there are many README files targeting different aspects, it helps to refer directly to the one associated with the specific Azure service or tool you are interested in for detailed instructions and information.
